Reasoning: The paper discusses memory-based meta-learning algorithms for building sample-efficient strategies that can adapt to any task within a target class. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). Given the focus on algorithmic templates for building predictors and reinforcement learners, as well as the Bayesian framework for recasting memory-based meta-learning, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. However, the potential applications to robotics, systems and control, and computer vision suggest that these sub-categories are also relevant.
